To add two numbers in base 3, we can align them and add each column starting from the right. 

\[
\begin{array}{c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}c}
 & & & 1 & 0 & 2 & 1 & 1 & 2 & 2 & 0 & 0 & 2_{3} \\
 & & + & 1 & 1 & 0 & 1 & 2 & 1 & 0 & 2 & 1 & 1_{3} \\
\cline{2-13}
 & & & 1 & 1 & 3 & 3 & 0 & 3 & 2 & 2 & 1 & 3_{3} \\
\end{array}
\]

Therefore, \( 1021122002_{3} + 1101210211_{3} = 11330322113_{3} \).